ers / editregionscheme        Opens an 'edit' window for a region colour scheme
 
   Format:
      ;ers <name>             Edits the sceme
 
   Notes:
      A region colour scheme defines a set of colours for one or more regions.
         The automapper window uses these colours when it draws the region(s).   
      <name> is the name of the scheme to edit. If it contains spaces, you
         should enclose the name in diamond brackets <...>.
 
   User commands:
      ers / editrs / editregionscheme
